Wanted to give you an update on the count in #PA01. There are still tens of thousands of mail-in ballots that need to be tabulated by county officials here. 

I urge patience. 

We must trust the democratic process and count every vote.

The campaign is over. It’s now time that we listen to the will of the people. 

So get some sleep tonight, and let's hope for big victories for Democrats up and down the ballot. I will have more to share once we know more. 

Thank you.

Thank you to my husband, my parents, & my daughters--who understood mommy was on a mission for the past 1.5 yrs.

This was a team effort. I hope I made you proud. I hope I WILL make you proud.

As the count continues, I urge patience and trust in the democratic process.

I want to thank everyone who made this effort possible. Thank you to all of my supporters, volunteers, staff, interns, and of course, all of the municipal Democratic committees across Bucks & Montco. 

Thank you to everyone who donated to our grassroots campaign.
Then the hard work begins. I am ready to work for you. All of you in Pennsylvania’s First District -- no matter who you voted for in this election.

This has been an unprecedented election. Pennsylvanians have turned out in record numbers to make their voices heard.
 
Don’t forget: In 2018, SE PA elected 4 Democratic women to Congress. As the results come in, I believe that we’ll be on our way to turning Fab 4 into the Fab 5.

From the latest data, we predict a record-breaking 400K ballots will have been cast in this race incl. ~200K mail-in ballots. Counting & adding them to the final tabulation will take time. We must let the hardworking public servants of PA-1 complete their important duties.
